  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Marine Assistant/Executive",
  "description": "<p>1. Marine / QHSE</p><p>- Directly support the Marine Manager & Superintendents in Vessel Operations</p><p>- Manage and maintain an up-to-date marine documentation and filing system</p><p>- Summarize fleet ships’ monthly/quarterly reports and records as required</p><p>- Assist in monitoring the Fleet KPI.</p><p>- Format and send circulars/alerts & best practices to ships. Follow up with vessels to receive feedback. Compile and assist the Marine Manager/DPA in summarizing and analyzing data</p><p>- Download and promulgate Flag circulars to vessels and upload them in the System and keep it up to date</p><p>- Monitor drug and alcohol test fleet-wide validity and arrange tests accordingly (involving liaising with contractor, agents, etc., for smooth and timely coordination)</p><p>- Record and maintain weekly and monthly meeting minutes</p><p>- Payment Arrangement (Management Company invoice) and following up</p><p>- Assist in organizing documents required by TMSA</p><p>2. Security</p><p>- Liaise with CSO for monitoring security threats and communicate with vessels</p><p>- Format and send security circulars and alerts to ships</p><p>- Arrange armed guards for vessels transiting in the High Risk Areas</p><p>- Complete security related questionnaire required by the charterer</p><p>- Liaise with the legal department for AWRP and K&R insurance arrangement, etc and input in the system as required</p><p>- Payment Arrangement for Security</p><p>3. Vetting</p><p>- Maintain Q88 database</p><p>- Send Q88 offline questionnaire for updating twice a month or as required</p><p>4. All other day to day works, and assist in other administrative matters as and when directed</p><p>Requirements:</p><p>· Diploma / Degree in related studies with a minimum of 1 year’s experience.<br /></p><p>· No experience are welcome to apply.</p><p>· Excellent knowledge of shipping operations.</p><p>· Able to work in a team environment independently with minimum supervision.</p><p>· Able to communicate in English, and it is a plus if able to communicate in Chinese (in order to liaise with Chinese-speaking associates and use the Chinese system).</p><p>· Must be able to commit extra hours as and when needed.</p>",
